California Privacy Rights
If you are a California resident, you may have certain rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), including the right to:
Request access to the personal information we have collected about you in the past 12 months;
Request that we delete the personal information we have collected about you, subject to certain exceptions;
Opt out of the sale of your personal information, if applicable; and
Be free from discrimination for exercising your privacy rights.
To exercise your rights under the CCPA, please contact us using the contact information provided in Section "Contact Information" above. We may require you to verify your identity before processing your request.
European Union and United Kingdom Privacy Rights
If you are a resident of the European Union (EU) or the United Kingdom (UK), you may have certain rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) or the UK Data Protection Act, including the right to:
Request access to, correction of, or erasure of your personal information;
Request the restriction of processing of your personal information;
Object to the processing of your personal information, including for direct marketing purposes;
Receive your personal information in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format, and transmit that information to another controller;
Withdraw your consent to the processing of your personal information, where your consent is the basis for processing; and
Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
To exercise your rights under the GDPR or the UK Data Protection Act, please contact us using the contact information provided in Section "Contact Information" above. We may require you to verify your identity before processing your request.
